                    "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/comment\/31488",
                    "author": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=sidedoor",
                        "name": "sidedoor",
                        "displayName": "John Fraboni",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "body": "This is not an issue with Zendamf, but rather Zend_Db, and to resolve the issue I enforced the character set of the persistent db connection to UTF-8 by using the following statement in the Zend_Db::factory parameters:\n\n'driver_options' => array(PDO::MYSQL_ATTR_INIT_COMMAND => 'SET NAMES utf8')\n\nThis issue can be deleted, thank you!",
